{{/*
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  WHAT  : files inside the chezmoi source tree that should NOT be applied
          to the target ($HOME).
  WHERE : home/.chezmoiignore  (chezmoi reads it as a template — the
          `{{` directives below get evaluated at apply time).
  WHY   :
    * .gitkeep stubs only exist so empty leaf dirs survive in git.
    * Defensive entries (README.md…) catch stray files dropped inside
      home/ by mistake.
    * OS-specific paths: VSCode lives at ~/.config/Code on Linux/macOS but
      %APPDATA%\Code on Windows. We ship BOTH templates and ignore the
      irrelevant one based on .chezmoi.os.
    * Editor opt-in: if the user did not tick "code" / "zed" / "nvim" in
      the TUI (`.editors`), the corresponding config tree never lands in
      $HOME — keeping the system clean of stuff the user did not ask for.
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*/ -}}

# Empty-dir markers — kept in git, never apply to $HOME.
**/.gitkeep

# Defensive: anything below would leak documentation/build cruft into $HOME
# if it ever ended up inside home/.
README.md
README.*
LICENSE
LICENSE.*
PLAN.md
docs
scripts

# ── OS gating ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{{- if eq .chezmoi.os "windows" }}
.config/Code
.config/zed
{{- else }}
AppData
{{- end }}

# ── Editor opt-in gating ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
{{- if not (has "code" .editors) }}
.config/Code
AppData/Roaming/Code
{{- end }}
{{- if not (has "zed" .editors) }}
.config/zed
{{- end }}
{{- if not (has "nvim" .editors) }}
.config/nvim
{{- end }}
